This article is a statement by the President on the certification of the repeal of the "Don't Ask, Don't Tell" law. The President states that this law undermines military readiness and violates principles of fairness and equality. He has certified and notified Congress that the requirements for repeal have been met, and the law will officially end on September 20, 2011. The President expresses confidence that the military will transition to the new policy in an orderly manner, preserving unit cohesion and military effectiveness. He commends the civilian and military leadership for their careful approach and thanks all service members, including those who are gay or lesbian, for their professionalism and patriotism during this transition. The President believes that this change will make the military stronger and reflect the values of justice and equality that define America. The article also includes certification and transmittal letters related to the repeal.